item.title: U.S. Eases Flight Ban on Chinese Airlines
item.description: The Trump administration eased off a plan to block all flights by mainland Chinese airlines to the U.S. after China said it would permit some passenger flights by U.S. airlines.

item.title: IAEA Voices Concern Over Iran Blocking Inspector Access to Sites
item.description: The United Nations atomic agency raised alarms about Tehran’s failure to let inspectors access two sites or answer questions about possible undeclared material. The watchdog also reported another big jump in Iran’s nuclear-fuel stockpile.

item.title: U.S. Coronavirus Deaths Pass 108,000; India Reports Its Highest Daily Toll
item.description: Brazil reported another record daily death toll and is now No. 3 in coronavirus deaths after the U.S. and the U.K.

item.title: China and India Try to Ease Border Tensions
item.description: China and India are elevating talks between military leaders to try to calm tensions along their disputed borders in the Himalayan mountains.

item.title: Brexit Talks Stall, Prompting Leaders to Intervene
item.description: U.K. Prime Minister Boris Johnson is set to hold talks with top Brussels officials later this month in a bid to break an impasse in negotiations on a post-Brexit trade deal, after the latest round ended with no major breakthrough.

item.title: Putin Declares Emergency Over Massive Arctic Fuel Spill
item.description: Investigators have launched a criminal probe into a spill at a power plant after the Russian leader upbraided a senior official for his handling of the incident.
